Prototype Enhancement
- The prototype enhancement proposes adding contextual game intensity weighting to the Player Fatigue Risk Index.
What Is Being Changed
- Instead of treating all game minutes equally, minutes played in high-intensity situations (e.g., overtime, short rest games, high-leverage matchups) would receive greater weight in the fatigue calculation.
Why This Improves Decision-Making
-This refinement better reflects the true physiological and mental load on players, allowing staff to distinguish between “quiet” playing time and high-stress workloads that accelerate fatigue and injury risk.


Reflection on Innovation and Version Control
- GitHub branches support low-risk experimentation by allowing analytics teams to explore enhancements without disrupting stable ideas already shared with stakeholders. This mirrors how organizations test concepts before committing resources.
- GitHub also helps analytics ideas gain traction by creating transparency, documentation, and a clear history of iteration—making it easier for decision makers to understand how and why an idea evolved.
- In General, this workflow closely aligns with Alamar (2024) Chapter 7 on innovation framework by supporting the creative, prototyping, engagement, and build phases in a structured, collaborative, and adoption-focused manner.

References
Alamar, B. C. (2024). Sports analytics: A guide for coaches, managers, and other decision
